title Operation Classes — Trig Methods Added

class NormalOperations <<static>> {
  + {static} add(a, b): float
  + {static} subtract(a, b): float
  + {static} multiply(a, b): float
  + {static} divide(a, b): float
  + {static} square(x): float
  + {static} square_root(x): float
}

class ScientificOperations <<static>> {
  + {static} power(base, exp): float
  + {static} cube(x): float
  + {static} cube_root(x): float
  + {static} factorial(x): int
  + {static} logarithm(x): float
  + {static} natural_logarithm(x): float
  + {static} sin(x: float): float
  + {static} cos(x: float): float
  + {static} tan(x: float): float
  + {static} cot(x: float): float
  + {static} asin(x: float): float
  + {static} acos(x: float): float
}

class Calculator {
  + add(a, b): float
  + subtract(a, b): float
  + multiply(a, b): float
  + divide(a, b): float
  + square(x): float
  + square_root(x): float
  + power(base, exp): float
  + cube(x): float
  + cube_root(x): float
  + factorial(x): int
  + logarithm(x): float
  + natural_logarithm(x): float
  + sin(x: float): float
  + cos(x: float): float
  + tan(x: float): float
  + cot(x: float): float
  + asin(x: float): float
  + acos(x: float): float
}

note right of ScientificOperations
  NEW: sin, cos, tan, cot, asin, acos
  asin/acos: requires x in [-1, 1]
  cot: sin(x) != 0 guard
end note

Calculator ..> NormalOperations : delegates
Calculator ..> ScientificOperations : delegates

@enduml
